descriptiveMetadata.title: On the Quadrature of Curves

names.fullForm: Portsmouth, Isaac Newton Wallop, Earl of, 1825-1891

descriptiveMetadata.abstract:
Miscellaneous drafts, notes and fragments regarding 'The Quadrature of Curves' (published 1706).


Some of the texts are published in D.T. Whiteside, The mathematical papers of Isaac Newton, Cambridge, 1967-1981, VII.
subject: Geometry - Early works to 1800
Mathematics - Early works to 1800
ownership: From the Portsmouth Collection, donated by the fifth Earl of Portsmouth, 1872.

descriptiveMetadata.title: Fragment On the Quadrature of Curves
descriptiveMetadata.abstract:
f.39 should go after f.54. ff.45-46 Draft of the Demonstratio on p.14 of the printed text.


f.31r, f.38ar-38bv and f.40r form part of the 'unfinished preliminary text' collated in D.T. Whiteside, The mathematical papers of Isaac Newton, Cambridge, 1967-1981, VII, 1.1, pp.24-48.


ff.29r-30v form part of the 'revised and augmented treatise on quadrature' collated in D.T. Whiteside, The mathematical papers of Isaac Newton, Cambridge, 1967-1981, VII, 1.2, pp.48-129.

descriptiveMetadata.title: Miscellaneous Papers On the Quadrature of Curves
descriptiveMetadata.abstract:
ff.51 contains draft of prop. VIII theor. VI and Prop.IX theor VII.


f.56r-v forms part of the 'unfinished preliminary text' collated in D.T. Whiteside, The mathematical papers of Isaac Newton, Cambridge, 1967-1981, VII, 1.1, pp.24-48.


f.55r and 56v-57v form part of the 'revised and augmented treatise on quadrature' collated in D.T. Whiteside, The mathematical papers of Isaac Newton, Cambridge, 1967-1981, VII, 1.2, pp.48-129.
